        "rendered": "Twenty Fifteen"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/themes/twentyfifteen\">Twenty Fifteen</a> is the default theme for WordPress in 2015. It is super-clean, content-focused, and designed to bring a little more simplicity to our blogs. Its careful attention to typography, featuring the expertly-designed <a href=\"http://www.google.com/get/noto/\">Noto font set</a> in elegant and harmonious margins, makes it beautiful in multiple languages around the world.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Twenty Fifteen looks great on devices of all sizes, from desktop to mobile and everything in between. The theme adapts to any screen without sacrificing usability or design integrity.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/750px-Responsive_Twenty_Fifteen.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"750\" height=\"280\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/750px-Responsive_Twenty_Fifteen.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10863617\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/750px-Responsive_Twenty_Fifteen.png 750w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/750px-Responsive_Twenty_Fifteen-300x112.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow\">\n<p><strong>Quick Specs (all measurements in pixels)</strong></p>\n</blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>There are a few ways that you can customize Twenty Fifteen, all from WordPress&#8217; Customizer. This short guide will show you how to:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>choose a featured color scheme</li>\n\n\n\n<li>add descriptions to your menus</li>\n\n\n\n<li>add social icons in your menu</li>\n\n\n\n<li>add block patterns</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Choose a featured color scheme</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Twenty Fifteen has six color schemes you can use to change the look of your blog. The Default color scheme is a light gray, but you can also choose from Dark, Yellow, Pink, Purple, and Blue.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/750px-Twenty_Fifteen_Colors.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"750\" height=\"503\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/750px-Twenty_Fifteen_Colors.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10863619\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/750px-Twenty_Fifteen_Colors.png 750w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/750px-Twenty_Fifteen_Colors-300x201.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To choose your color scheme, go to <strong>Appearance &gt; Customize</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Under &#8220;Colors&#8221;, select your preferred color scheme from the drop down:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/Twenty_Fifteen_Customize_Color_Schemes.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"330\" height=\"479\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/Twenty_Fifteen_Customize_Color_Schemes.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10863622\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/Twenty_Fifteen_Customize_Color_Schemes.png 330w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/Twenty_Fifteen_Customize_Color_Schemes-207x300.png 207w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 330px) 100vw, 330px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;ll see the color scheme change in the preview pane to the right.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you&#8217;re done, click <strong>Save and Publish</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Add Menu descriptions</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Twenty Fifteen has a menu design that\u2019s easy to navigate, especially when you add menu descriptions.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/Twenty_Fifteen_Menu.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"448\" height=\"770\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/Twenty_Fifteen_Menu.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10863623\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/Twenty_Fifteen_Menu.png 448w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/Twenty_Fifteen_Menu-175x300.png 175w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 448px) 100vw, 448px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To start adding descriptions to your menus, go to <strong>Appearance &gt; Menus</strong> and <strong>click the Screen Options tab</strong> in the upper right of the screen.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the &#8220;Show advanced menu properties&#8221; section, <strong>check the box</strong> next to Description.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/750px-Twenty_Fifteen_Screen_Options.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"750\" height=\"151\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/750px-Twenty_Fifteen_Screen_Options.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10863620\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/750px-Twenty_Fifteen_Screen_Options.png 750w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/750px-Twenty_Fifteen_Screen_Options-300x60.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now you can begin adding descriptions to any link in a menu.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/Twenty_Fifteen_Menu_Descriptions.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"433\" height=\"467\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/Twenty_Fifteen_Menu_Descriptions.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10863624\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/Twenty_Fifteen_Menu_Descriptions.png 433w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/Twenty_Fifteen_Menu_Descriptions-278x300.png 278w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 433px) 100vw, 433px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When you&#8217;re done, click <strong>Save Menu</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Add social icons</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Twenty Fifteen also allows you to display links to your social media profiles with crisp, perfectly-sized icons.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can see these icons at the bottom of the menu displayed in the previous section.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step is to go to <strong>Appearance &gt; Menus</strong> and <strong>create a new menu</strong> &#8211; you can name your menu anything you like.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You will then add the URL for each social profile to your menu as a custom link.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you have added all desired links, <strong>click Save Menu</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you have created your menu and added your social links, <strong>go to the Manage Locations tab</strong> and next to &#8220;Social Links Menu&#8221;, select the social icons menu you just created from the drop down.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/750px-Twenty_Fifteen_Social_Icons_Manage_Menu.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"750\" height=\"213\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/750px-Twenty_Fifteen_Social_Icons_Manage_Menu.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10863621\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/750px-Twenty_Fifteen_Social_Icons_Manage_Menu.png 750w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2018/11/750px-Twenty_Fifteen_Social_Icons_Manage_Menu-300x85.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Click Save Changes</strong> when you\u2019re done.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Available icons</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Linking to any of the following sites will automatically display its icon in your menu:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>CodePen</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Digg</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Dribbble</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Dropbox</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Email (mailto: links)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Facebook</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Flickr</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Foursquare</li>\n\n\n\n<li>GitHub</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Google+</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Instagram</li>\n\n\n\n<li>LinkedIn</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Path</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Pinterest</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Pocket</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Polldaddy</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Reddit</li>\n\n\n\n<li>RSS Feed (URLs with /feed/</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Spotify</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Skype</li>\n\n\n\n<li>StumbleUpon</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Tumblr</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Twitch</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Twitter</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Vimeo</li>\n\n\n\n<li>WordPress</li>\n\n\n\n<li>YouTube</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Add Block Patterns</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Twenty Fifteen comes bundled with a set of <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/block-pattern/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/block-pattern/\">block patterns</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can access the block patterns from the Block Editor.</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Click the + icon to add a new block.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Click on the <em>Patterns</em> tab.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Select <em>Twenty Fifteen</em> from the drop down menu.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Click on the pattern you wish to insert and the pattern is inserted in the document at the location of your cursor.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"619\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2021/06/twenty-fifteen-block-patterns-1024x619.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-14592874\" style=\"width:732px;height:442px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2021/06/twenty-fifteen-block-patterns-1024x619.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2021/06/twenty-fifteen-block-patterns-300x181.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2021/06/twenty-fifteen-block-patterns-768x464.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2021/06/twenty-fifteen-block-patterns.png 1120w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Block patterns in Twenty Fifteen</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What else can you do?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also use the Customizer to make the following changes to your website:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Change your Custom Header image</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Featured Images: works best with images that are 825px wide by 510px high</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Change the background image or color</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Set a static front page</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also select a gradient option for certain blocks that fit the theme color scheme:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"932\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/02/208979102-b9bc9bb3-bc66-490e-9052-0eb60f0ff985-932x1024.png\" alt=\"Select a gradient option for certain blocks\" class=\"wp-image-16355687\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/02/208979102-b9bc9bb3-bc66-490e-9052-0eb60f0ff985-932x1024.png 932w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/02/208979102-b9bc9bb3-bc66-490e-9052-0eb60f0ff985-273x300.png 273w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/02/208979102-b9bc9bb3-bc66-490e-9052-0eb60f0ff985-768x844.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/02/208979102-b9bc9bb3-bc66-490e-9052-0eb60f0ff985.png 1172w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 932px) 100vw, 932px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Links</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/themes/twentyfifteen/\">Twenty Fifteen Demo and Download</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/twenty-fifteen-changelog/\">Twenty Fifteen Changelog</a></li>\n</ul>\n",
